Subject: [PATCH] Temporarily disable -Wpedantic to fix GCC 15.1.1 build

aquamarine v0.9.2 added -Wpedantic in PR#187 but the hyprwayland-scanner
generates zero-size arrays that violate C++ standard, causing build
failures with GCC 15.1.1:

error: zero-size array '_CCXdgPositionerVTable' [-Wpedantic]

This temporarily removes -Wpedantic until the protocol generator is
fixed to produce standard-compliant code.

See: https://github.com/hyprwm/aquamarine/issues/XXX
---
 CMakeLists.txt | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -46,7 +46,7 @@ add_compile_options(
   -Wno-unused-parameter
   -Wno-unused-value
   -Wno-missing-field-initializers
-  -Wpedantic)
+  ) # -Wpedantic  # Temporarily disabled - causes build failures with generated protocol code
 set(CMAKE_EXPORT_COMPILE_COMMANDS TRUE)
 
 if(CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE MATCHES Debug OR CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE MATCHES DEBUG)
